    "why": "BLAKE2s-256 is the one crypto primitive ts_tunnel uses that has no direct KAT elsewhere. It backs the WireGuard Noise_IKpsk2 transcript hash, the mac1/mac2 cookie MACs, and the HKDF chaining-key expansion (ts_tunnel/src/handshake.rs imports blake2::{Blake2s256, Digest}; ts_tunnel/src/macs.rs; ts_tka SigHash). The Wycheproof project ships no BLAKE2 set, so this is sourced from the canonical BLAKE2 reference KAT instead.",
