    "convention": "Canonical BLAKE2 KAT: an input of length n is the bytes 00 01 02 ... (n-1). Keyed vectors use the fixed 32-byte key 00 01 02 ... 1f. Keyed BLAKE2s is a MAC construction parameterized by the key (blake2::Blake2sMac256 via KeyInit), NOT a hash over key||input.",
